   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER ONE THE ORIGIN OF THE BODY OF CHRIST Scripture Reading: Gal 4:6; Rom 8:15; John 1:12-13; 1 Pet 1:2a; Luke 15:8, 17; John 16:8-11; 3:5-6; Rom 8:19; 1 Cor 6:15; 12:27; Col 3:4a; 1 John 1:2; 5:11-12; John 3:36a; Matt 28:19; 1 Cor 12:13a; Col 2:9; John 1:14a; Heb 2:14a, 17-18; John 14:16-17; 7:39; Rev 22:17a; 1 Cor 15:3-4, 45b; John 15:1, 5; 17:21a, 23a OUTLINE God the Father being the believers' source Gal 4:6; Rom 8:15: Who are begotten of God the Father John 1:13.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Who become the children of God the Father John 1:12.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>God the Spirit sanctifying and regenerating the ones selected and predestinated by God the Father: Sanctifying them 1 Pet 1:2a: Enlightening and seeking them Luke 15:8, 17.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Convicting the enlightened ones John 16:8-11.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Regenerating them John 3:5-6: To be the sons of God Rom 8:19.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>To be the members of Christ 1 Cor 6:15; 12:27.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>God the Son being life to the regenerated ones Col 3:4a: For the members of Christ to receive the uncreated and eternal life of God 1 John 1:2; 5:11-12; John 3:36a.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Bringing the members of Christ into an organic union with the Triune God Matt 28:19.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>The Father, the Son, and the Spirit becoming the consummated Spirit who baptizes the members of Christ into the unique Body of Christ 1 Cor 12:13a: The Father being embodied in the Son Col 2:9: Passing through incarnation John 1:14a; Heb 2:14a.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Experiencing human life Heb 2:17-18.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>The Son realized as the Spirit John 14:16-17: The Spirit being the consummated Spirit John 7:39.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>The Spirit being the ultimate consummation of the Triune God Rev 22:17a: Having passed through death and resurrection 1 Cor 15:3-4.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Becoming the all-inclusive, life-giving, indwelling, and compound Spirit 1 Cor 15:45b.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Baptizing all the sanctified and regenerated ones into the Body of Christ 1 Cor 12:13a: Baptizing the regenerated ones into the Triune God Matt 28:19.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Making them one with the Triune God to be the Body of Christ John 17:21a, 23a.</S>
   </TEXT>
